{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh macadamias into it. Cover with water and set aside to soak overnight.","Preheat oven to 30°C (see Tips). Using simmering basket, drain macadamias and set aside.","Place coconut oil into mixing bowl and warm <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add drained macadamias and kefir and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and repeat blending <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend for a further <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr> or until combined. Transfer mixture into a large sterilised glass jar (large enough to allow mixture to increase in volume) and cover with lid (but do not seal). Place jar into oven for 6 hours (30°C), then turn off oven and leave in oven overnight to ferment. It should bubble and increase in size a little. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Line a plate with paper towel and set aside.","Place eschalot, garlic, oil, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then cook <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer onto prepared plate and allow to cool (approx. 30 minutes).","Place chives, reserved garlic mixture and reserved fermented cheese into mixing bowl and combine <nobr>8 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture into a bowl and place into refrigerator until firm (approx. 2 hours - see Tips). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Divide mixture into halves and shape each half into a ball.","Place pecans into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Press chopped pecans onto the outside of the cheese balls. Wrap balls in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g whole macadamia nuts","water, for soaking","3 tsp coconut oil","90 g kefir (coconut)","50 g eschalot","1 garlic clove","1 tbsp olive oil","½ tsp salt","ground black pepper, to season","1 tbsp fresh chives, finely chopped","60 g pecans, roasted"]}],"id":"r145663","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-NntScxaLFSY\/XZaqy6T_1CI\/AAAAAAAAhhE\/Lr2Bfi84_wE-rRz0TbXY6N_sbPutPdvQQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nqOwNcG84KE0j1jQ.png","title":"Vegan macadamia cheese ball","publishedAt":"2017-04-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.8 g","fat":"28 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"2.2 g","calories":"1156 kJ \/ 275 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, sealable sterilised jar, 1 plate, paper towel, plastic wrap, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Ensure that your jar is sterilised (either dishwasher method or boiling water method) before adding macadamia cheese mixture.","If you prefer not to use your oven (or if your oven temperature does not go as low as 30°C), place in a warm\/sunny place and leave to ferment as per recipe. It will become porous and airy when ready.","Once cheese is firm (after refrigeration), you can store in refrigerator and use as needed (omitting shaping into balls and chopping pecans). Cheese will last for up to 1 week in the refrigerator."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","56h 55m","8 portions"]}